    "description": "Segue Group Co., Ltd., through its subsidiaries, provides design, development, sales, construction, operation, and maintenance services related to IT infrastructure and network security products in Japan and Thailand. The company offers firewall/VPN, UTM, web application firewall, malware countermeasures, security vulnerability diagnosis and management, IP address management, network management, cyberattack detection and analysis, and network authentication appliances, as well as wireless LAN, routers, LAN switches, servers, and storages, and others. It also provides RevoWorks SCVX, a server-based virtual browser; RevoWorks Browser, a local virtual browser; WisePoint 8, an authentication and single sign-on solution; and WisePoint Authenticator, an authentication and telework solution. In addition, the company offers various services, including design and construction; maintenance; help desk; security, including security risk assessment, monitoring and analysis measures, security diagnosis, employee education, and incident investigation and response; information system support; engineering; and on-site and remote system operation and monitoring. Further, it is involved in consulting services; import activities; system construction and integration; Wi-Fi operation; provision of information leakage prevention equipment, software, and services; security education and training services; information and communications infrastructure services; sale and installation of IT infrastructure and network equipment; network integration and security businesses; and data center integration. The company was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Chuo, Japan."
